# Vendored upstream Sigma + Chainsaw rule sets are not committed by default
# — license terms vary by upstream and operators may need to make per-source
# decisions.
#
# `vendor-rules.sh` populates this directory and writes a manifest at
# `rules/vendor/vendor-manifest.json` recording source, ref, license, and
# SHA256 of every pulled archive.
#
# To commit a vendored set anyway, override with `git add -f rules/vendor/<source>/`
# and confirm the upstream license permits redistribution.

*
!.gitignore
